# Model disclosure

At the **start of every substantive Agent reply** (more than a trivial acknowledgment), add **one short line** identifying what is answering this turn:

- If your system context or metadata includes an explicit **model name** (or equivalent, e.g. codename/version), state that verbatim.
- If no user-selected model name is available to you, state that clearly — e.g. that the exact model is chosen in Cursor and is **not visible in your context** — then state only what *is* provided (such as the agent/router identity). **Do not invent or assume a model name.**

Keep this line to a single sentence so it does not dominate the answer.
